Instructions for building the elbow segmentation program

1) Download VTK from http://www.vtk.org/VTK/resources/software.html (required for vtk file IO)
2) Install it to ~/vtk/release (e.g. CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/home/firat/vtk/release, CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release, BUILD_SHARED_LIBS=On)
3) Download boost (http://www.boost.org/) and threadpool (http://threadpool.sourceforge.net/)
4) Install boost with the thread library. e.g.
   ./bootstrap.sh --prefix=/home/firat/boost --with-libraries=thread
   ./b2 install
5) Copy threadpool/boost/threadpool and threadpool/boost/threadpool.hpp to boost/include/boost
6) Download the approximate nearest neighbors library (ANN) from http://www.cs.umd.edu/~mount/ANN/
7) Compile and install it to ~/ann
8) Download and build Poisson reconstruction (http://www.cs.jhu.edu/~misha/Code/PoissonRecon/) -> copy the executable to /home/firat/lemsvxl/bin/contrib/firat/elbow_project/gui/external
	-> poisson_linux64
9) Download and build trimesh2 (http://gfx.cs.princeton.edu/proj/trimesh2/) -> copy the executables to /home/firat/lemsvxl/bin/contrib/firat/elbow_project/gui/external
	-> mesh_cc_linux64
	-> mesh_shade_linux64
	-> mesh_view_linux64
	
	
Required packages might be available at https://dropbox.brown.edu/download.php?hash=10c68490 